00:10:16.830 --> 00:10:22.050
I want to tell you a little bit
about the trials and tribulations

00:10:22.050 --> 00:10:25.970
of writing a biography in Iran.

00:10:25.970 --> 00:10:29.490
Of writing a woman's
biography in Iran.

00:10:29.490 --> 00:10:35.120
And in particular in writing
Forough Farrokhzhad's biography.

00:10:35.120 --> 00:10:41.410
I believe she is the most
talked-about Iranian woman.

00:10:41.410 --> 00:10:45.670
I Googled her about a month ago.

00:10:45.670 --> 00:10:47.310
I was going to do it last night.

00:10:47.310 --> 00:10:49.960
I didn't get a chance
to be up to date.

00:10:49.960 --> 00:10:57.750
But a month ago if you do a Scholar
Google, Forough Farrokhzhad has

00:10:57.750 --> 00:11:04.960
about twice as many hits
as Mohammad Reza Pahlavi

00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:09.610
who ruled Iran for 37 years.

00:11:09.610 --> 00:11:15.540
So it would be fair to say that
she has become quite popular

00:11:15.540 --> 00:11:18.700
and she's talked about.

00:11:18.700 --> 00:11:23.590
And finally I would like
to share with you some

00:11:23.590 --> 00:11:26.180
of her unpublished letters

00:11:26.180 --> 00:11:30.490
that I have collected
over the last 37 years.

00:11:30.490 --> 00:11:34.620
And that it had taken me
so long to finally decide

00:11:34.620 --> 00:11:39.840
that maybe I'm not invading
her privacy to publish them.

00:11:39.840 --> 00:11:43.980
I have been in possession
of some of these letters,

00:11:43.980 --> 00:11:47.460
not all of them, for a long time.

00:11:47.460 --> 00:11:49.930
But because they were so personal,

00:11:49.930 --> 00:11:54.980
I wasn't sure it's the
right thing to publish them.

00:11:54.980 --> 00:12:01.560
But given the fact that there is
so much misinformation about her.

00:12:01.560 --> 00:12:11.240
There is the fact that it's almost
a half a century after her death.

00:12:11.240 --> 00:12:18.040
I thought maybe it would be the
right thing to publish this,

00:12:18.040 --> 00:12:24.630
about 100 pages of unpublished
letters along with the biography.

00:12:24.630 --> 00:12:30.150
So what do we know about
Farrokhzhad's early life?

00:12:30.150 --> 00:12:39.000
You have probably as her
birthday January of 1935.

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:40.700
It's not the right birthday.

00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:43.760
There is so many misinformation
about her.

00:12:43.760 --> 00:12:48.320
And I'm not sure I can figure
out why, but they're out there.

00:12:48.320 --> 00:12:50.980
I have seen her birth certificate.

00:12:50.980 --> 00:12:55.280
So with certainty I can
tell you that she was born

00:12:55.280 --> 00:13:02.870
on Saturday the 29th
of December 1934.

00:13:02.870 --> 00:13:07.640
She was born to Turan Vezitabar

00:13:07.640 --> 00:13:11.240
and Muhammad Farrokhzhad
Aroki [assumed spelling].

00:13:11.240 --> 00:13:19.210
You will see again in Farrokhzhad's
document her name is Forough

00:13:19.210 --> 00:13:21.480
Kazemoni Farrokhzhad
Aroki [assumed spelling].

00:13:21.480 --> 00:13:25.720
That's her birth certificate.

00:13:25.720 --> 00:13:35.730
And I will get to why Aroki,
where does that come from.

00:13:35.730 --> 00:13:40.630
The child was born Forough
Kosimon [assumes spelling],

00:13:40.630 --> 00:13:46.350
which significantly
means eternal light.

00:13:46.350 --> 00:13:49.750
And of course the occasion
of the birth

00:13:49.750 --> 00:13:54.360
of a child is always
a jubilant occasion.

00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:56.530
And hers was too.

00:13:56.530 --> 00:14:03.110
Except that it was marred by
the absence of the father.

00:14:03.110 --> 00:14:15.520
Lieutenant Muhammed Farrokhzhad
at the time was in prison.

00:14:15.520 --> 00:14:23.090
And he was the head of Pahlavi
royal properties, [inaudible].

00:14:23.090 --> 00:14:35.360
And for some reason he and a few
others had been put in prison.

00:14:35.360 --> 00:14:39.790
So when Forough was
born, he was not there

00:14:39.790 --> 00:14:46.780
to welcome his daughter
who was his third child.

00:14:46.780 --> 00:14:53.300
So Mr. Farrokhzhad was released
from prison after a year.

00:14:53.300 --> 00:14:56.890
And like the paradoxical
country that Iran is,

00:14:56.890 --> 00:15:03.110
after a year of imprisonment he
returned to his position in Yoshat

00:15:03.110 --> 00:15:09.260 position:56%
as the head of the Pahlavi property.

00:15:09.260 --> 00:15:15.180
So Farrokhzhad was born in Tehran
but she spent the first six years

00:15:15.180 --> 00:15:23.270 position:56%
of her life not in Tehran but in
Nowshahr, which is the northern part

00:15:23.270 --> 00:15:26.310
of Tehran in the province
of Mazandaran.

00:15:26.310 --> 00:15:29.340 position:56%
They lived in a beautiful big house.

00:15:29.340 --> 00:15:33.000
In fact, in front of the
castle of [inaudible].

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:35.610
On one side was a forest.

00:15:35.610 --> 00:15:41.150
On the other side was
the Caspian Sea.

00:15:41.150 --> 00:15:44.580
And Forough loved the forest.

00:15:44.580 --> 00:15:50.980
And apparently she was constantly
running through the forest.

00:15:50.980 --> 00:15:55.240
What we might not know and
I didn't know for a while is

00:15:55.240 --> 00:16:02.780
that Forough was stunningly
beautiful as a baby, as a girl.

00:16:02.780 --> 00:16:10.280
She had fair complexion, big
black eyes and curly hair.

00:16:10.280 --> 00:16:13.170
Blond, curly hair.

00:16:13.170 --> 00:16:16.670
Kind of unusual for Iran.

00:16:16.670 --> 00:16:22.900
And lovingly and I would say
ironically she was called

00:16:22.900 --> 00:16:24.840
Out of Sight Fradanki.

00:16:24.840 --> 00:16:35.110 position:56%
Now I say ironically because this
little girl was anything but a doll.

00:16:36.250 --> 00:16:42.270
She refused to be commandeered
by strings like a marionette.

00:16:42.270 --> 00:16:49.770
Throughout her life and beginning
from her very early childhood,

00:16:49.770 --> 00:16:57.230
the prospect of becoming
a puppet horrified her.

00:16:57.230 --> 00:17:00.090
She had a will of her own.

00:17:01.200 --> 00:17:07.260
She was willful, determined,
tenacious.

00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:13.200
I will tell you, I have interviewed
over 60 people, her family members,

00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:17.670
her close friends and
some of her colleagues.

00:17:17.670 --> 00:17:22.570
And most of the information
I give you today are things

00:17:22.570 --> 00:17:25.190
that I have cross-referenced.

00:17:25.190 --> 00:17:28.830 position:56%
I've heard some things, if they
were not cross-referenced I've tried

00:17:28.830 --> 00:17:31.970
to avoid saying them.

00:17:31.970 --> 00:17:37.300 position:56%
But almost any people who knew her
as a child told me that first of all

00:17:37.300 --> 00:17:40.540
when they were in Nowshahr
she preferred the forest.

00:17:40.540 --> 00:17:44.850
And when they moved to Tehran
when she was six years old,

00:17:44.850 --> 00:17:47.950
she preferred the street.

00:17:47.950 --> 00:17:55.990
She was constantly fighting boys
and often gave them a good beating.

00:17:55.990 --> 00:18:00.960
She scaled walls.

00:18:00.960 --> 00:18:02.820
I've heard from a couple of people

00:18:02.820 --> 00:18:07.420
that she was like little
[inaudible].

00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:11.760
Agile like a cat.

00:18:11.760 --> 00:18:18.770
Really nimble with
gravity-defying agility.

00:18:18.770 --> 00:18:20.360
She jumped.

00:18:20.360 --> 00:18:23.310
She climbed trees.

00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:32.250
This is not image of a young
girl in Iran of the '30's.

00:18:32.250 --> 00:18:36.120
She was fearless and daring.

00:18:36.120 --> 00:18:41.660
And these words basically
didn't exist in her lexicon.

00:18:47.040 --> 00:18:48.560
A little bit about
Forough's parents,

00:18:48.560 --> 00:18:54.360
because they in their own right
are really fascinating people

00:18:54.360 --> 00:18:57.440
and we don't hear about them.

00:18:57.440 --> 00:19:02.070
In particular, we barely
every hear about the mother

00:19:02.070 --> 00:19:06.390
who was a fascinating woman.

00:19:06.390 --> 00:19:10.340
She too was a subversive woman.

00:19:10.340 --> 00:19:13.910
She was born in 1913.

00:19:13.910 --> 00:19:19.420
She was unveiled before
the Underling Act of 1936.

00:19:19.420 --> 00:19:24.110
She went to the American
school in Tehran.

00:19:24.110 --> 00:19:31.270
She was not yet 16 when
at a party in the house

00:19:31.270 --> 00:19:41.930
of her relative she met this young
Lieutenant Mohammed Farrokhzhad

00:19:41.930 --> 00:19:46.330
who was 11 years older.

00:19:46.330 --> 00:19:52.400
She fell in love with him
and he fell in love with her.

00:19:52.400 --> 00:20:00.100
Turan had lost her father
before she was even born.

00:20:00.100 --> 00:20:04.480
Her mother, lovely mother, and in
fact Forough has a few references

00:20:04.480 --> 00:20:06.920
to her grandmother in her poetry.

00:20:06.920 --> 00:20:11.820 position:56%
And the more I've learned about
[Foreign name], the more I have come

00:20:11.820 --> 00:20:16.400
to appreciate those lines about the
grandmother in Forough's poetry.

00:20:16.400 --> 00:20:23.130
Both of them were very
opposed to this wedding.

00:20:23.130 --> 00:20:29.230
But she was adamant she
wanted to marry him.

00:20:29.230 --> 00:20:31.710
And they did.

00:20:31.710 --> 00:20:37.520
Turan was a very hardworking woman.

00:20:37.520 --> 00:20:40.140 position:56%
Everybody talks about her proclivity

00:20:40.140 --> 00:20:45.250
for outspoken simplicity
and honesty.

00:20:45.250 --> 00:20:50.370
She had a hard time lying,
as her daughter will later.

00:20:50.370 --> 00:20:54.080
I think one of the most
beautiful characteristics

00:20:54.080 --> 00:20:58.260
of Forough Farrakhzhad
is her incapacity to lie.

00:20:58.260 --> 00:21:00.150
I'm not saying she never lied.

00:21:00.150 --> 00:21:03.610
Such a person probably
doesn't exist.

00:21:03.610 --> 00:21:08.620
But in a culture of walls and
veils and masks and masquerades,

00:21:08.620 --> 00:21:16.410
Forough Farrakhzhad was herself
as much as it was possible to be.

00:21:16.410 --> 00:21:21.440
Once she was chosen as
the mother of the year.

00:21:21.440 --> 00:21:23.430
This is her.

00:21:23.430 --> 00:21:27.270
This is before the age of 24.

00:21:27.270 --> 00:21:29.910
She had already four children.

00:21:29.910 --> 00:21:36.150
And by the age of 35
she had seven children.

00:21:36.150 --> 00:21:41.790
And she had a few pregnancies
that did not go to full term.

00:21:41.790 --> 00:21:43.290
Now what about the father?

00:21:43.290 --> 00:21:46.510
Let me tell you one
other thing that I find

00:21:46.510 --> 00:21:51.910
so fascinating about
Turan Farrakhzhad.

00:21:51.910 --> 00:21:54.660
She was a doll collector.

00:21:54.660 --> 00:21:58.800
And because dolls are so
central again in Forough's life

00:21:58.800 --> 00:22:00.690
and in Forough's poetry, one

00:22:00.690 --> 00:22:03.370
of her most beautiful
poems is [foreign words],

00:22:03.370 --> 00:22:06.420
"One Can Be Like a Doll."

