00:42:03.640 --> 00:42:07.720
And if you read the biographical
sketch, it's all about the fact

00:42:07.720 --> 00:42:10.260
that this is a married woman.

00:42:10.260 --> 00:42:13.590
She has a child who
is two years old.

00:42:13.590 --> 00:42:16.250
She has beautiful disheveled hair.

00:42:16.250 --> 00:42:21.390
She has beautiful black
eyes that are penetrating.

00:42:21.390 --> 00:42:28.990
So the focus is on her body
and on her marital status.

00:42:28.990 --> 00:42:38.910 position:56%
So in other words, whoever wrote
that early piece wanted to make sure

00:42:40.390 --> 00:42:47.710
that this woman committed
this pleasurable act of union

00:42:47.710 --> 00:42:52.410
with a man who is not her husband.

00:42:52.410 --> 00:43:00.640
The layout of the magazine turns a
poem into a testimonial of sorts.

00:43:00.640 --> 00:43:03.090
It's almost like a report.

00:43:10.190 --> 00:43:19.570
At the time, many Iranian
poets had chosen pseudonyms.

00:43:19.570 --> 00:43:22.760
Forough Farrakhzhad
